snippet: McKayla Maroney won gold after edging out all-around champion Simone Biles in the vault.
abstract: United States women's gymnastics team wins a second gold-silver double in two days at the world championships in Antwerp, Belgium, with the defending champion McKayla Maroney beating the all-around champion Simone Biles in the vault.
lead_paragraph: McKayla Maroney won gold after edging out all-around champion Simone Biles in the vault.

headline.main: Maroney Wins World Title in Vault
